<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Autoencoder for Dimensionality Reduction | World Happiness Report 2023</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            background: #e2e8f0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            min-height: 100vh;
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', 'Roboto', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;
            padding: 24px;
        }

        .poster {
            width: 794px;
            min-height: 1123px;
            background: white;
            box-shadow: 0 20px 35px -12px rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
            border-radius: 8px;
            overflow: hidden;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
        }

        .content {
            padding: 28px 32px 36px 32px;
            flex: 1;
        }

        .title-section {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            border-bottom: 3px solid #2563eb;
            padding-bottom: 14px;
        }
        .main-title {
            font-size: 28px;
            font-weight: 800;
            color: #0f172a;
            letter-spacing: -0.5px;
        }
        .subtitle {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #2563eb;
            font-weight: 500;
            margin-top: 6px;
        }
        .byline {
            font-size: 11px;
            color: #475569;
            margin-top: 4px;
        }

        .two-columns {
            display: flex;
            gap: 20px;
            margin: 16px 0 12px 0;
        }
        .col {
            flex: 1;
        }

        .card {
            background: #f8fafc;
            border-radius: 16px;
            padding: 12px 14px;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
        }
        .card-title {
            font-size: 15px;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #1e40af;
            border-left: 3px solid #3b82f6;
            padding-left: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        .card-text {
            font-size: 11px;
            line-height: 1.4;
            color: #1e293b;
            text-align: justify;
        }
        .metric-list {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            gap: 6px;
            margin-top: 8px;
        }
        .metric-badge {
            background: #dbeafe;
            border-radius: 30px;
            padding: 3px 10px;
            font-size: 9px;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: #1e40af;
        }

        .fig {
            margin: 10px 0 6px 0;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .fig img {
            max-width: 100%;
            border-radius: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
            background: white;
        }
        .fig-caption {
            font-size: 9px;
            color: #64748b;
            margin-top: 4px;
            font-style: italic;
        }

        .stats-row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 12px;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }
        .stat-box {
            flex: 1;
            background: #ffffff;
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 8px 4px;
            text-align: center;
            border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;
        }
        .stat-number {
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: 800;
            color: #1e40af;
        }
        .stat-label {
            font-size: 9px;
            color: #475569;
        }

        .conclusion {
            background: #eef2ff;
            padding: 14px 18px;
            border-radius: 16px;
            margin-top: 12px;
            border-left: 4px solid #2563eb;
        }
        .footer-note {
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 9px;
            color: #64748b;
            border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
            padding-top: 12px;
            margin-top: 8px;
        }
        hr {
            margin: 8px 0;
        }
        @media print {
            body {
                background: white;
                padding: 0;
                margin: 0;
            }
            .poster {
                box-shadow: none;
                width: 100%;
                height: auto;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="poster">
    <div class="content">
        <!-- Title Section -->
        <div class="title-section">
            <div class="main-title">🌍 Autoencoder for Nonlinear Dimensionality Reduction</div>
            <div class="subtitle">Compressing 6 Socioeconomic Indicators into 2D Latent Space | World Happiness Report 2023</div>
            <div class="byline">Unsupervised Learning | Optimization Strategies | Country Clustering Analysis</div>
        </div>

        <div class="two-columns">
            <!-- Left Column -->
            <div class="col">
                <!-- What is Autoencoder -->
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-title">🧠 What is an Autoencoder?</div>
                    <div class="card-text">
                        An autoencoder is a neural network that learns efficient <strong>nonlinear dimensionality reduction</strong>. It consists of an <strong>encoder</strong> that compresses input data into a low-dimensional <strong>latent space</strong>, and a <strong>decoder</strong> that reconstructs the original input. By minimizing reconstruction error, it captures the most important features while discarding noise.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Dataset -->
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-title">📊 Dataset: 6D Socioeconomic Indicators</div>
                    <div class="card-text">
                        150+ countries from the <strong>World Happiness Report 2023</strong>. Each country is described by 6 features:
                    </div>
                    <div class="metric-list">
                        <span class="metric-badge">GDP per capita</span>
                        <span class="metric-badge">Social support</span>
                        <span class="metric-badge">Health expectancy</span>
                        <span class="metric-badge">Freedom</span>
                        <span class="metric-badge">Generosity</span>
                        <span class="metric-badge">Corruption perception</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Learning Rate Comparison -->
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-title">🎯 Learning Rate Tuning</div>
                    <div class="fig">
                        <img src="learning_rate_comparison.png" alt="Learning Rate Comparison" style="width:100%;">
                        <div class="fig-caption">▲ Figure 1: Loss curves for different learning rates. lr=0.01 achieves optimal convergence.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-text">
                        A learning rate of <strong>0.01</strong> provides the best balance — fast convergence without oscillation or divergence.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Optimizer Comparison -->
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-title">⚙️ Optimizer Comparison</div>
                    <div class="fig">
                        <img src="optimizer_comparison.png" alt="Optimizer Comparison" style="width:100%;">
                        <div class="fig-caption">▲ Figure 2: Training loss curves for SGD, Adam, and RMSprop.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-text">
                        <strong>RMSprop</strong> significantly outperforms both SGD and Adam, achieving the fastest convergence and lowest reconstruction error.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Right Column -->
            <div class="col">
                <!-- Training Loss Curve -->
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-title">📉 Training Loss Curve</div>
                    <div class="fig">
                        <img src="loss_curve.png" alt="Training Loss Curve" style="width:100%;">
                        <div class="fig-caption">▲ Figure 3: Training loss with RMSprop and lr=0.01 — rapid initial drop followed by smooth convergence.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-text">
                        The loss decreases sharply in early epochs and stabilizes without oscillations, confirming optimal hyperparameter selection.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Latent Space Visualization -->
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-title">🗺️ 2D Latent Space: Country Clusters</div>
                    <div class="fig">
                        <img src="latent_space.png" alt="Latent Space" style="width:100%;">
                        <div class="fig-caption">▲ Figure 4: 2D representation of all countries in latent space.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="fig">
                        <img src="latent_clustering.png" alt="Latent Clustering" style="width:100%;">
                        <div class="fig-caption">▲ Figure 5: Country clusters — Nordic and Western European countries form tight groups.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-text">
                        Countries with similar socioeconomic characteristics naturally cluster together. High-happiness countries (e.g., Finland) appear in distinct regions.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Latent Correlation -->
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-title">📐 Latent Dimensions Correlation</div>
                    <div class="fig">
                        <img src="latent_correlation.png" alt="Latent Correlation" style="width:100%;">
                        <div class="fig-caption">▲ Figure 6: Correlation analysis between Latent Dim 1 and Dim 2.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stats-row">
                        <div class="stat-box">
                            <div class="stat-number">-0.142</div>
                            <div class="stat-label">Correlation Coefficient</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="stat-box">
                            <div class="stat-number">Negative</div>
                            <div class="stat-label">Relationship</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Second Row: Feature Analysis -->
        <div class="two-columns">
            <div class="col">
                <!-- Feature Contribution -->
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-title">🔍 Feature Contribution Analysis</div>
                    <div class="fig">
                        <img src="feature_contribution.png" alt="Feature Contribution" style="width:100%;">
                        <div class="fig-caption">▲ Figure 7: Contribution of original features to hidden layer nodes.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-text">
                        <strong>Freedom, social support, and GDP</strong> show the highest contribution weights — these are the key drivers of national happiness.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Feature Heatmap -->
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-title">🔥 Hidden Layer Feature Mapping</div>
                    <div class="fig">
                        <img src="feature_heatmap.png" alt="Feature Heatmap" style="width:100%;">
                        <div class="fig-caption">▲ Figure 8: Heatmap of feature contributions to hidden layer nodes.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col">
                <!-- Latent Statistics -->
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-title">📊 Latent Space Statistics</div>
                    <div class="fig">
                        <img src="latent_statistics.png" alt="Latent Statistics" style="width:100%;">
                        <div class="fig-caption">▲ Table 1: Statistical summary of latent dimensions.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-text">
                        Both latent dimensions approximate normal distributions, indicating well-decoupled and structured representations.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Correlation Heatmap -->
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-title">🔗 Full Correlation Analysis</div>
                    <div class="fig">
                        <img src="correlation_heatmap.png" alt="Correlation Heatmap" style="width:100%;">
                        <div class="fig-caption">▲ Figure 9: Correlation matrix of original features, happiness score, and latent dimensions.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-text">
                        <strong>Latent Dim 1</strong> correlates positively with GDP and social support. <strong>Latent Dim 2</strong> correlates negatively with freedom and corruption perception — revealing complementary semantic dimensions.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Conclusion -->
        <div class="conclusion">
            <div style="font-weight: 800; font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px;">✅ Key Findings & Conclusion</div>
            <div class="card-text" style="color: #0f172a;">
                • <strong>RMSprop + lr=0.01</strong> achieved optimal training performance with fastest convergence and lowest reconstruction error.<br>
                • The autoencoder successfully compressed 6D happiness indicators into a <strong>2D interpretable latent space</strong>.<br>
                • Countries with similar socioeconomic profiles form <strong>natural clusters</strong>, revealing global patterns.<br>
                • Latent dimensions capture complementary aspects: <strong>economic development (Dim1)</strong> and <strong>social freedom (Dim2)</strong>.<br>
                • Autoencoders provide a powerful <strong>nonlinear alternative</strong> to traditional DR methods like PCA and t-SNE.
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="footer-note">
            🧪 Experiment: Fully-connected autoencoder | Loss: MSE | Optimizer: RMSprop | Learning Rate: 0.01 | Epochs: 200
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
